32:27.439 --> 32:32.203
from Laredo Junior College. And West Texas, of 
course, was in difficulty. Their enrollment was

32:36.627 --> 32:38.108
down. Excuse me, was this acquisition, would you 
say, at least in part at the initiative of the A&M

32:39.151 --> 32:50.344
Regents, or what was the attitude there? But I know 
there were conflicts. I would say it was more a

32:53.127 --> 32:58.813
passive act. Let me answer it this way. It was not a 
situation where the A&M system had an overall

33:01.817 --> 33:08.044
long-range strategy. and saw these institutions 
as important components that, if they could be

33:08.665 --> 33:18.255
acquired, would help to promote that long-term 
strategy. There was no long-term strategy for the

33:18.295 --> 33:23.080
system. In fact, what the system mostly did was,

33:23.100 --> 33:37.255
what we call, ensure fiduciary integrity. manage 
the books, carry out audit functions, invest

33:38.095 --> 33:52.435
money for the common good, manage our share of the 
permanent university fund and the AUF. And

33:54.619 --> 34:01.849
together with the regents, hire and fire 
