low engineering, low agriculture, no

36:25.456 --> 36:33.345
engineering, no agriculture? and what the 
quality was as indicated by the admissions SAT

36:34.068 --> 36:50.724
scores of entering students, kind of came to the 
conclusion that a number of these universities

36:34.068 --> 36:50.724
didn't really fit our system. And I think there was 
some sentiment at that time that the study was done

36:50.744 --> 37:03.737
in part to defend the system against other 
institutions being given to us. So the idea was try

37:04.223 --> 37:24.040
to come up with some rationale so that if

37:04.223 --> 37:24.040
some institution, Sol Ross or whatever, decides 
they want to join, you can say, yeah, that makes

37:04.223 --> 37:24.040
sense, ignore it. No, it doesn't. Well, that study 
was finished. And then Perry announced he was

37:30.045 --> 37:32.948
going and stepped down. So everything was kind of 
put on hold pending the arrival of the new

37:34.089 --> 37:42.798
chancellor. As part of that process, though, 
there had been established a committee, a regent

37:44.520 --> 37:59.695
committee on strategic planning and long-range 
goals and strategic planning headed by Raul

37:44.520 --> 37:59.695
Fernandez. So the mechanism was in place. And when 
Bill Mobley was here with Perry, he had initiated a

38:03.987 --> 38:20.256
comprehensive strategic planning process for 
the whole system. And there had been one

38:20.497 --> 38:21.879
iteration. So that was in place.

