38:36.193 --> 38:38.096
A&M system anyway? What do we want it to be? What's 
its mission in the state as compared with other

38:40.139 --> 38:44.926
systems? Particularly, how is it different from 
the UT system in terms of the missions and goals?

38:52.918 --> 38:57.846
And we had a whole series of meetings with the 
Regents Planning Committee, and with our CEOs,

38:58.214 --> 39:05.260
agency directors, and presidents on that issue. 
The outcome of that was a short statement of what

39:05.301 --> 39:18.112
the A&M system is, besides being a collection of 15 
institutions. Do you have that somewhere? Yes, I

39:19.494 --> 39:22.256
do. We also have a vision statement that It 
expresses what some of our values are, things like

39:29.011 --> 39:50.036
being a premier source of

39:29.011 --> 39:50.036
education, research, and new technology

39:29.011 --> 39:50.036
