of, whatever they were, the financial tensions on

40:38.319 --> 40:46.787
the systems and higher education generally in 
Texas. Because I know every school wanted to

40:46.807 --> 40:56.055
re-enact itself to something to get a portion of 
the available funds, et cetera, et cetera. And we

40:57.554 --> 41:09.004
have some collaborative research programs 
between UT and A&M. In engineering, for instance,

41:10.605 --> 41:27.240
the Offshore Technology Center, NTS,

41:10.605 --> 41:27.240
the Southwestern University Transportation 
Research Center, NTTI. It's a collaboration

41:27.811 --> 41:33.878
between A&M and UT Austin. And there are others. 
There's a space grant consortium.

