What about you? I think in terms of new directions, 
I see my job, a lot of my job is to encourage

43:01.700 --> 43:22.786
collaboration and synergy among these 15 
institutions that we have. So that each president

43:22.846 --> 43:30.175
or CEO has a sense of dual citizenship. One, of 
course, is as the leader in their particular unit,

43:31.859 --> 43:45.497
whether it's Texas A&M University or it's the Ag 
Extension Service, but also to feel a sense of

43:31.859 --> 43:45.497
citizenship in the system as a whole. So that while 
they need to look inward and look to the support of

43:48.160 --> 43:59.875
their units and the growth and development of 
their units, they also have to look upward and

43:48.160 --> 43:59.875
outward with a responsibility to help the system 
as a whole be more and do more than the collection of

44:00.732 --> 44:12.788
the individual parts can. We're in a very enviable 
position in a lot of ways because of the presence of

44:12.808 --> 44:26.527
these statewide research and service agencies in 
engineering and agriculture. They provide, in a

44:26.547 --> 44:30.452
lot of ways, the web or the network that encourages 
institutions to work together.

